        "description": "Free API connect to https://www.ecb.europa.eu",
        "servers": [
          {
            "url": "https://api.exchangerate.host"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Exchange Rate API",
        "version": "1.0.0",
        "tagline": "Free EUR-centric foreign exchange rates sourced from the European Central Bank",
        "homepage": "https://api.exchangerate.host",
        "docs_url": "https://www.exchangerate.host",
        "license_short": "Proprietary terms; consult exchangerate.host (APILayer) Terms of Service.",
        "license_md": "- Operated by [exchangerate.host](https://www.exchangerate.host), an APILayer product.\n- Underlying ECB reference rates are public information from the European Central Bank.\n- No explicit attribution requirement is documented on the catalogue page; review the provider's Terms of Service before redistribution.\n- Usage is subject to the API plan you sign up for (free and paid tiers).",
        "about_md": "[Exchange Rate API](https://api.exchangerate.host) is a REST service that exposes current and historical foreign exchange rates, with rates derived from the [European Central Bank](https://www.ecb.europa.eu/) and other financial data providers. The service is run by [APILayer](https://apilayer.com/).\n\nWhat you get from the API:\n- Latest exchange rates for EUR against a list of supported currencies\n- Cross-rate lookups starting from a chosen base currency\n- A directory of supported currency symbols\n- Historical end-of-day rates over a date range, with selectable frequency\n\nOperational notes: historical rates are end-of-day values timestamped at 23:59 GMT, with roughly 19 years of history available. The free tier is capped at 100 requests per month, and response headers report current rate-limit usage. The community catalogue at [freepublicapis.com](https://freepublicapis.com/euro-rates-api) notes that CORS is disabled across endpoints.",
        "entity_desc": {
          "currency": "A supported currency, typically identified by its ISO 4217 code, used as the base or target of a rate lookup.",
          "exchange_rate": "A foreign exchange rate quote between two currencies, available either as the latest value or as a historical end-of-day series."
        },
        "auth": false
